metadata.description:
The Second Narration:  
"A profound melancholy suddenly hit me. What precious memories were left imprisoned in these vessels, never to be shared anymore? Surely one knew the soothing smile of the beloved. Surely one contemplated the grandeur of the sea. Surely one experienced the sadness of a lost friendship. Millions of tales never to be told again, forever locked inside rotten pieces of organic flesh. Fragments of life that only eyes can tell but now forever mute."
